 Friday, March 04, 2005 

 Blair was keen on rock career

 London, March 3 (Reuters): Running the UK is all well and good, but Tony Blair still wonders if he could have made it as a rock star. If only he?d had the attitude...

 ?I?ve always wondered, could I have actually ever done it,? the one-time lead singer of a rock band called the Ugly Rumours, more recently Prime Minister of Britain, told his former bass player in an interview published today.

 ?I was quite serious about it. It wasn?t just a mere dalliance,? Blair told ex-bass player Mark Ellen in The Times newspaper. ?With politics, it all clicked into place for me somehow. Whereas with music you had to have a particular set of attitudes that I didn?t quite have, and it never happened for me even though I was keen to carry on.? 




